---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import CtaBand from '../components/CtaBand.astro';
import { site, telLink, mailLink } from '../data/site';

const title = 'Terms of Service | TJ Mods (Proper Mods Ltd) East London';
const description =
  'The terms on which TJ Mods (Proper Mods Ltd) provides its car modification services and this website. Quotations confirmed after inspection.';
const lastUpdated = '02/06/2026';
---
<Layout title={title} description={description} current="/terms">
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms of Service"
    subtitle="The terms on which we provide our services and this website. Please read them carefully."
    crumb="Terms of Service"
  />

  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="legal-prose fade-in">
        <p class="mono text-[0.82rem] uppercase tracking-wider text-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

        <h2>1. Acceptance of these terms</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of this website and the basis on which we provide our services.
          By using this website or enquiring about or booking our services, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree
          with them, please do not use the site or our services.
        </p>

        <h2>2. About us</h2>
        <p>
          This website and our services are provided by <strong>{site.legalName}</strong>, trading as
          <strong>{site.name}</strong> ("we", "us", "our"), a car modification studio based at {site.address.street},
          {site.address.area}, {site.address.city} {site.address.postcode}, United Kingdom. You can reach us by phone on
          <a href={telLink}>{site.phoneDisplay}</a> or by email at <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Our services</h2>
        <p>
          We offer vehicle modification services including window tinting, car wrapping, paint protection film, parking
          sensors, car audio, lighting upgrades and vehicle security. The descriptions on this website are provided for
          general information only. All work is <strong>subject to an initial consultation, inspection of your vehicle and a
          written quotation</strong> before it is agreed and carried out. We will discuss your requirements with you and
          recommend the most suitable option for your vehicle.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Quotations and prices</h2>
        <p>
          Any prices or estimates we mention - whether on this website, by phone or by message - are
          <strong>indicative only</strong> until confirmed in a written quotation. A quotation is based on the information
          available to us and the condition of your vehicle at the time. Once you accept a written quotation and we confirm
          your booking, that becomes the agreed price for the work described. If the scope of work changes, or additional
          work is needed once we inspect the vehicle, we will discuss this and agree any revised price with you before
          proceeding.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Bookings and cancellations</h2>
        <p>
          Bookings are confirmed once we have agreed a date and the work to be done. If you need to change or cancel a
          booking, please let us know as early as possible so we can offer the slot to another customer. We may ask for a
          deposit for certain work; where we do, the terms of that deposit will be made clear at the time of booking.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Your responsibilities</h2>
        <p>To help us carry out the work safely and correctly, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>provide accurate and complete information about yourself and your vehicle;</li>
          <li>ensure you are the owner of the vehicle, or are authorised by the owner to commission the work;</li>
          <li>provide relevant vehicle documentation where we reasonably request it;</li>
          <li>remove personal belongings and valuables from the vehicle before it is left with us; and</li>
          <li>make us aware of any existing damage, defects or modifications relevant to the work.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Workmanship and aftercare</h2>
        <p>
          We carry out our work with reasonable care and skill. Films, wraps and other products are fitted and cared for in
          line with the relevant manufacturer's and film supplier's guidance. To keep your modification looking its best, we
          will provide aftercare advice (for example, recommended periods before washing a freshly applied film or wrap).
          Following this guidance is important - failure to do so may affect the finish and any product or workmanship cover
          that applies.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for any loss or damage that is not a foreseeable result
          of our breach of these Terms, for business losses, or for the condition of pre-existing paintwork, glass, trim or
          components that are affected by their prior state rather than by our work.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Nothing in these Terms limits or excludes our liability where it would be unlawful to do so.</strong> This
          includes liability for death or personal injury caused by our negligence, for fraud or fraudulent
          misrepresentation, and any other liability that cannot be limited or excluded under the laws of England and Wales.
          Your statutory rights as a consumer are not affected by these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          The content of this website - including text, design, graphics, logos and images - is owned by or licensed to
          {site.legalName} and is protected by intellectual property laws. You may view and print pages for your own
          personal, non-commercial use. You may not reproduce, distribute or otherwise use any content for commercial
          purposes without our prior written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Third-party links</h2>
        <p>
          This website may contain links to third-party websites and services (such as Google Maps, WhatsApp and our social
          media profiles) for your convenience. We do not control these third parties and are not responsible for their
          content, availability or practices. Following any external link is at your own risk and subject to that third
          party's own terms and policies.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Privacy and cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Our use of your personal data and cookies is explained in our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> and
          <a href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>, which form part of these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms, and any dispute or claim arising out of or in connection with them, are governed by the laws of
          <strong>England and Wales</strong>, and are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and
          Wales.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. The version published on this page, with its "Last updated" date,
          is the version that applies. We recommend you review this page periodically.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact <strong>{site.legalName}</strong> (trading as
          {site.name}) at {site.address.street}, {site.address.area}, {site.address.city} {site.address.postcode}, by email
          at <a href={mailLink}>{site.email}</a>, or by phone on <a href={telLink}>{site.phoneDisplay}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    title="Talk to us about your project"
    text="The best way to get an accurate price is a quick chat and a look at your car. Call, message us on WhatsApp, or visit our Ilford studio for a no-obligation quote."
  />
</Layout>
